    {
      "parameters": {
        "promptType": "define",
        "text": "=Extract basic metadata from this document in valid JSON format.\n\nDOCUMENT:\n{{ $('Code in JavaScript').first().json.document }}\n\nExtract:\n1. **Title**: Clear, descriptive title for this document\n2. **Summary**: One sentence describing what compliance information this provides (max 150 characters)\n3. **Effective Date**: Extract any date mentioned as effective date, publication date, or revision date in YYYY-MM-DD format. If none found, use null.\n4. **Key Terms**: List 5-10 important terms, phrases, or concepts mentioned in the document (agencies, programs, regulations, locations, activities)\n\nOUTPUT (JSON only):\n{\n  \"title\": \"title here\",\n  \"summary\": \"summary here\",\n  \"effective_date\": \"YYYY-MM-DD or null\",\n  \"key_terms\": [\"term1\", \"term2\", \"term3\", \"term4\", \"term5\"]\n}\n",
        "options": {}
